</code></pre>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-03-14T23:12:15.735Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":10.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":430285,"topic_slug":"jittering-between-default-command-and-configurebuttonbindings","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":8002,"username":"Akash_Rastogi","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/akash_rastogi/{size}/169937_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":55681,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/jittering-between-default-command-and-configurebuttonbindings/430285/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3164840,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-14T23:34:14.781Z","cooked":"<p>I suspect what’s happening is your isFinished() returns true, which ends the command, which results in setting the motors to 0.  Then the command gets rescheduled because the button is still pressed, which runs the motors for one cycle before the process repeats.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-03-14T23:34:14.781Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":21,"readers_count":20,"score":9.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":430285,"topic_slug":"jittering-between-default-command-and-configurebuttonbindings","display_username":"Peter Johnson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":55681,"username":"GetWellSune","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/d9b06d/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":13575,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Volunteer WPILib Developer, CSA"},"post_url":"/t/jittering-between-default-command-and-configurebuttonbindings/430285/5","custom_user_title":"Volunteer WPILib Developer, CSA","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3164995,"name":"Andy Gasser","username":"gdefender","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-15T03:09:32.078Z","cooked":"<p>Since you didn’t share enough code I can’t say for sure, but based on what you shared it looks like you’re referencing your <code>ArmSubsystem</code> statically, even though you’re passing an instance into the <code>ArmSliderTopCmd</code>. I’m basing this on the fact that you have the A capitalized, and I assume this code compiles.</p>
<p>The command-based system uses the requirements to know that a command needs a subsystem. I have no way of knowing, but you might have more than one instance (or no instances) of <code>ArmSubsystem</code>, so the framework may not know this command requires the arm. If this happened, you could have more than one command running that uses the arm at the same time.</p>
<p>Additionally, these two binds look weird, but again, you didn’t share enough of the code to know what’s going on:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">new JoystickButton(secondaryJoystick, 5).onTrue(
    new ArmIntakeInCmd(armSubsystem, () -&gt; secondaryJoystick.getRawButton(5)));
new JoystickButton(secondaryJoystick, 6).onTrue(
    new ArmIntakeOutCmd(armSubsystem, () -&gt; secondaryJoystick.getRawButton(6)));
</code></pre>
<p>Why are you passing a lambda that reads the joystick button? If you want to cancel the command when the button is released, use <code>whileTrue()</code> instead of <code>onTrue()</code>.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-03-15T03:09:32.078Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":16,"readers_count":15,"score":3.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":430285,"topic_slug":"jittering-between-default-command-and-configurebuttonbindings","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":13575,"username":"Peter_Johnson","name":"Peter Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/jittering-between-default-command-and-configurebuttonbindings/430285/6","custom_user_title":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3332668,"name":"system","username":"system","avatar_template":"/uploads/default/original/4X/9/3/2/93234578e69f55873c63fc00fe2d0d85f23bce55.png","created_at":"2024-03-14T03:09:58.480Z","cooked":"<p>This topic was automatically closed 365 days after the last reply. New replies are no longer allowed.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":3,"pos